reviewText: The story is fine, the picture quality is grainy and the sound quality is horrible. The song from the title Jawani Zindabad will quickly become an earworm for you.  Lots of cheesy 80s goodness, with a moral about matchmaking and dowry's, which I can appreciate if not wholly relate to an a American.  Enjoyable for what its worth, but one time of watching it is probably enough for me.
